cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new algorithm for semi-supervised learning using support vector machines. It also involves theoretical analysis of the algorithm's convergence. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as semi-supervised learning is a subfield of AI. 

The paper's use of random features and gradient descent could place it in the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision) as these techniques are commonly used in image processing and computer vision. 

The use of large datasets and scalability could also place it in the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). 

Finally, the use of support vector machines and gradient descent could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these techniques are commonly used in neural networks and evolutionary algorithms.
